article.headline: Brown 75, Yale 65
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Jason Forte scored 29 points, including 16 on 18 free throw attempts, as Brown defeated Yale, 75-65, in the last game of the Ivy League season for both teams Tuesday. Freshman Damon Huffman added 18 points for the Bears (5-9, 12-16) who defeated the Bulldogs (7-7, 11-16) for the sixth game in a row and the eighth in the teams' last nine meetings. The loss prevented Yale from earning a share of second place with Cornell. Edwin Draughan led Yale with 22 points while Alex Gamboa added 11. Yale led 43-42 early in the second half when Brown went on a 12-4 run, including 3-pointers from Forte and Huffman. Gamboa hit a free throw to pull Yale within 60-57 with 5:36 remaining. But Marcus Becker hit two free throws and Huffman hit another 3-point shot to give Brown a 67-59 lead. Forte clinched the victory by sinking four of six free throws in the last 1:04. The Bears led only once in the first half, 19-18, on a fast-break basket by Forte. Yale outscored Brown 15-5 for a 33-24 lead as Gamboa hit a 3-point shot plus two free throws. Huffman's 3-point basket and two free throws by Forte enabled Brown to pull within 37-35 at halftime. Forte, a senior guard from Rockville, Md., finished his career as the third-leading scorer in Brown history with 1,597 points.
